quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  2,275,"Those who devour usury cannot stand{1}except as does one who is being beaten by Satan into insanity. That is because they said, “Trade and usury are certainly the same.” But Allah has permitted trade and has forbidden usury. Thus, to whomsoever an admonition came from his Lord, so he refrained<i>(from usury) </i>—then his past earnings belong to him and his matter rests with Allah. Yet whoever reverts—then those{2}are the fellows of the Fire; therein they abide.",1:[On the Day of Resurrection.],2:[A grammatical shift from singular to plural.]
  2,276,"Allah eliminates usury and He makes donations grow, for Allah does not love every sinning relentless denier."
  2,277,"Indeed, those who have attained faith and have done righteous deeds and have established the prayer and have brought{1}the purifying charity{2}—their reward is with their Lord, and no fear<sup>a </sup>shall beupon them nor shall they grieve.",1:[The Qur’an always uses verb ‘to bring’ rather than verb ‘to give’],2:[in association with charity; this should be pondered by the reader.]
  2,278,"O you who have attained faith, be mindful of Allah and leave aside what has remained of usury, if you are believers."
  2,279,"But if you<sup>pl </sup>do not, then be informed{1}of a war from Allah and His Messenger. Yet if you repent, then your capitals belong to you—<i>(thus) </i>you do no injustice, and you are not done injustice.",1:[Qira’at: Shu’ba and Hamza read it as: “…then inform (everyone) of a war…”]
  2,280,"But if he{1}has hardship, then deferment until a time of ease. But to donate{2}it is better for you<sup>pl </sup>, if you only knew.",1:[The debtor.],2:[To waive it as charity.]
  2,281,"And be mindful of a day{1}when you<sup>pl </sup>are returned{2}to Allah, then the earnings of every single self are rendered in full to it, for they{3}are not done injustice.",1:[Literally ‘guard yourselves against a day’.],2:[Qira’at: Abu Amr and Ya’qub read it as: “…when you return to Allah,”],3:[A grammatical shift from 2<sup><small>nd</small></sup> person to 3<sup><small>rd</small></sup> person.]
